<Time>1621574874562<//Time><rate>5<//rate><Review>The best things in life always survive, including Atami Sushi.  We have been going to Atami since 1999, and this family run business continues to maintain high quality delicious sushi with a friendly comfortable atmosphere.  Michelle and Wiley always make you feel welcome when you arrive and they remember your favorite selections.  The sushi is always fresh, the service is quick, and Michelle always keeps the restaurant extremely clean.  They have had a tough time fighting through the Covid shutdowns, so if you are in the neighborhood and want some great sushi in a cozy and friendly restaurant, you should stop on by and pay them a visit.  Also, this is a rarity in SF, but they have several parking spots for those coming from farther away.<//Review><Pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPeI05jg43UhuIA0T6t1u1REjx0FQNGUzJzm-r2=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMmQGXXeYHkR1Hdl11p1ONRPzHJ3GSpkpTHJOAJ=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMvA5zCkqCtbzwnF3tU30DiyZYfrRZvkY6wfO0r=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNM47pXt6TOAF0-zWW98yYkNAch-K8WvoWxwPAM=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOlZPSzpYLfIRKCDB11asJr-j9ATqgE6hMLUt8w=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipP4HSEU23YcZ8xFCY21ovGxGAUumhXPC1rr5WJ1=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMajpKvF2HkowDqC3NRH55yQjYyojL4NKdSvijy=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]</Pictures>< Response>

< Review>
My favorite restaurant on the planet. I have eaten here with friends and family at least 50 times and always had an excellent experience. This is a small family owned restaurant with amazing and authentic Japanese sushi. Yes, the portions are on the smaller site but the quality of the ingredients and the love of the owners for their customers more than makes up for this.
On some nights the service can be slow but just bring time and you won't be disappointed. This restaurant is all about taste and flavor, unlike so many Bay Area restaurants that sell mediocre food in a hipster ambiance for the same price.<//Review>

<GmapID>0x808580dc6e49ad11:0x60e45ffb6f3910a1</GmapID><text>I agree with Ian H: great sushi without the obnoxious scene.  The restaurant is set back from Lombard Street, behind a little stone garden and, while not ornately  decorated, is quiet and clean.  Service can be a little leisurely (usually because Michelle, an owner, is the only one serving tables) but the food is great.  The fish is quite fresh: sashimi pieces are smaller than you see at most restaurants but it's good stuff.  I don't usually order rolls when eating sushi but Atami's rolls use interesting fish (say no to Alaskan Rolls of salmon and cream cheese!) and are presented nicely.  Great sushi restaurant in a neighborhood of hits and (mostly) misses.< /text>< Pics>

< Text>
I dropped my friend off at this place so that she could do her laundry for free. They also have free bathrooms, showers 24 hours a day.

And if you go between 7AM and 7PM they allow you to do 1 load of your laundry and let you use their charging stations for your electronics.

Its amazing places like this exist.  I only used the bathroom and charged my phone while I waited for her to do her laundry.

They also take donations, I gave them a couple bags of clothes and hygiene items and they were very grateful.

While I waited, I watched this amazing artist freehand draw the most incredible piece of art, just breath taking work!

This place is located in skid row and the area looks intimidating but the people that go there and the employees are good people.< /Text>

I am beyond speechless Leaving this  restaurant. Thank you chipotle and there staff <3</text>

Normally I always listen to the ratings so I wasn‚Äôt expecting great service. I can honestly encourage seekers and followers of Jesus to gather together her and call this family of believers THEIR VERY OWN family of believers. <userid>105357814042384952046</userid><name>Allison Hunter< /name><date>1563053504935< /date><Rating>2<//Rating>< Text>
I've been here a couple of times now and I buy the same product every time, I usually get the Smokiez edibles sour apple gummies and I take them to help me with crushing panic disorder. Usually I take 1 gummy, and within 30-45 minutes I start to feel it in my system with the maximum effect hitting me in about 2 hours (as suggested on the package) and I'm usually very satisfied with how I feel after 1 dose. The last time I went here, a few days ago, they were out of the sour apple so I bought the regular apple. I've been taking them over the last few days and I have not felt like anything is happening at all. I called the store a few minutes ago and spoke to the manager, he kept insisting I try without eating beforehand, eating beforehand, try multiples of them at one time and says my tolerance may be going up, I repeatedly told him I've tried everything he is suggesting and I doubt that my tolerance is going up as I haven't been taking them for very long, maybe a few weeks to a month. But instead of offering a solution, we just kept going around and around him telling me to try different things and me saying I've already tried them and it's not helping me. He told me he hasn't had anyone else call about problems with the Smokiez edibles so I just have to keep trying what he suggested and hope it works out. I don't care if no one else has called about problems with a dud package, I JUST DID and my concerns were ignored. Another dispensary I've been to has flat out told me "If for any reason you aren't completely satisfied with your purchase, call us or come in and we will replace the product for you", yet I was not offered this at Dixon Wellness Collective. Very disappointing that instead of just offering to replace the product I purchased, I feel like I was being told it is MY fault the product I bought from them isn't working. I'm very disappointed and having worked in retail I can 100% tell you, if you offer to replace a product your customer says isnt working, it let's your customer know you're really listening to them and their concerns and letting them know that you take it seriously and want to bring them the best product possible, I feel like I was completely ignored by who I spoke to.
EDIT: I was looking at other reviews and I can see other customers notifying the store about problems with their product and the store offering to replace it for them. Now I'm more upset that I feel ignored and not taken seriously.<//Text>

< Review>
First off I would like to say that I have heard nothing but great reviews from friends of mine, I don‚Äôt know if I just had a bad experience but I am very disappointed. My meal was ok, I‚Äôm vegan and it‚Äôs a bit difficult to find dishes at most places but my food was ok. My mother who lived in Italy for years got Gnocchi. We grubhubbed it because our cars are in the shop. Her gnocchi looked vile and she couldn‚Äôt even finish it. It was super undercooked and had the consistency of melted cheese. <user>117315376558664984195< /user><user_name>Cherish Lah'Nique</user_name><Date>1618841440335</Date><Rating>5<//Rating><Review>This was my first time at Regal Carlsbad. When entering Theatre #12, there was two other people sitting in their seats. I was in shock of how the seats were & how much space in between the aisles. The seats are labeled in ABC order. So, my seats were G - 10 & G - 9. Our seats were 2 rows from the back wall of the theatre right in the middle. We sat down in our seats & they were so comfortable. They were recliner seats, so you can position the level of your legs and position your head too. There is a small desk that holds your drink and your snacks. A couple came and sat anywhere for a bit of time. Another couple came into the same row that the other couple was sitting in & told them that they were in their seats. My mom was a bit confused on how come they're allowing reserved seating when people aren't sitting in the seats that they paid for? <user_name>Jessica Southwick<//user_name><Date>1599319795271<//Date><Rate>1</Rate>< Text>
This is the best of the regal theaters which says a lot about the chain. They are always understaffed and it can take 40+ minutes to get a food order. Guaranteed 20-30 for a simple popcorn and candy. Mind you, you're paying outrageous theater prices for the bad service. These times have gotten worse since they closed the box office and made you buy tickets at concessions. Location is great at the mall and the recliners are nice though. Just plan to be there extremely early or don't get concessions and buy tickets through the app.< /Text>

Steven Davis< /name>
<Date>1580660512596<//Date>< rating>
5</rating>
< review>
As home theater equipment gets better and better, movie theaters are making the movie experience more home like with reclining chairs and menu items far beyond the popcorn and Coke of my youth. The Regal in Carlsbad does this as well as anyone in the area. The seats are comfortable and the snack bar is well stocked with a variety of junk food. To be sure, they have actual meals, but clearly on the junk food side - hey, it's a movie theater. Food is acceptable, but if you're coming to the Regal to eat, then you should be reading a review of mental hospitals and not movie theaters.</review>

Great place to see a movie. The seats are comfortable and have the ability to recline to your comfort. There is ample space in each aisle and between each seat to make sure you are always in comfort. The lower amount of seats in each theater help the environment from seeming too stuffy or crowded, even in a full house. Each seat has it's own tray so you have the perfect place to keep all of your movie snacks. And speaking of movie snacks, they have quite a few options to satisfy your hunger during your show. Prices are a little high for the tickets but food is reasonable for a movie theater.< /Review>

< Review>
Staff are cheerful and the place is spacious. The seats are by reservation and are the kind which recline and have a surface for your concessions.

Very cushy and comfy - I feel sometimes like I melt into their chairs.

My one complaint is that it's not easy to find the entrance. It's tucked close to the mall entrance with a small sign; there's a much larger sign visible from the street, but it'll lead you to the back of the building, and the only way around is by climbing over hedges or going through the whole mall.

Parking can be a bit tight if you go at peak hours due to sharing with the shops.</Review>

< text>
I went to watch a special screening of a movie tonight and the movie was great. The theater was not. The projector was not on for the first ten minutes of the film. Everyone was sitting in a dark theater only being able to hear the movie, not see it. Some people got up to tell the workers about it and finally the movie was projected on to the screen, but we had already missed out on the beginning and asked the projectionist, whose head stuck out the small window above the theater, if they could start the movie from the beginning. They looked around for a few seconds, then stuck they're head back in without saying a word and the movie continued like normal for a good couple of minutes until suddenly, without warning, it completely stopped. We then proceeded to wait another good couple of minutes staring at a blank screen until finally the movie began again, this time from the beginning. The whole thing took about half an hour. I don't like to complain, but through this whole ordeal NOBODY from the theater came in to tell us what was happening. They didn't explain or apologize for the lateness of the film and I just found that so odd and rude. I have had something similar happen to me at a different Regal location and the manager quickly came into the theater and explained what was happening and even offered to give us free vouchers for a future movie. At this theater though we were all left completely in the dark. I don't think I'll be coming back to this particular theater.< /text>

<Name>Nancy Chapman</Name>< Date>
1524512110005< /Date>
<Rate>5< /Rate>< review>
Much nicer than most Regal Cinemas I've watched movies at. There's plenty of parking, easy location to find, several enjoyable restaurants nearby if you'd like to have a bite before or after.

My favorite part is the seating.  You can choose ahead of time your seat location and they have several spots for wheelchair access. The seats are recliners, which was quite comfortable... especially as I am disabled.

As for the staff, I encountered several and they were all very polite.

The only drawbacks I saw during my visit was the crazy long, long lines at the concession counter which moved very slowly.  My server seemed as if I were talking to a robot and annoyed by the couple of questions I had about their items. But when she went to get my order, she and another employee seemed to have acquired a happier personality until she returned with my order. Once I'd paid for my items, I felt rushed to leave. Unfortunately, I am disabled and can only carry my items in one hand and use my pockets for smaller items. She was young and maybe this is her first job; I can understand that. But maybe a different change of positions (i.e. ticket taker) may suit her personality better.

Overall, I had a great experience with the one exception, which I will overlook because almost all other visits there were spot on.

‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ 5 star overall rating.< /review>

< Review>
Best Movie theater in San Diego area, period!

The staff was great as we were getting our popcorn. we didn't have to go through line to get our tickets,  wanna know why? Because we ordered our tickets online as they have reserved seats!  its perfect!. The building looks great and everything is brand spanking new.

The best part, RECLINING SEATS WITH A FOOD TRAY!. I was enjoying my time watching a movie, reclining and eating my popcorn, I felt like I was home or even better. The space between rows is so big that when people have to get up to the bathroom up you don't have to move a single inch. even while reclining :) .

I will be going to this theater more often, thank you Regal for not messing this one up!< /Review>

< Date>
1531955110389<//Date>
< Review>
The movie theater is well maintained and clean, I usually always buy my tickets via an app and then show up and scan said tickets from my phone which is very convenient.

The concessions can take a while though, so I advise you arrive 30-40min prior to your movie starting if you're looking to get snacks.

The seats are nice and comfortable but in some theaters they are starting to show their age due to wear and tear, loose trays, etc. But nothing major.

It's located in the Carlsbad mall space close to lots of shopping and dining, making parking a bit of a pain if you don't arrive with plenty of time to spare.

Overall solid movie theater with an enjoyable atmosphere for the whole family.</Review>

< Text>
Much nicer than most Regal Cinemas I've watched movies at. There's plenty of parking, easy location to find, several enjoyable restaurants nearby if you'd like to have a bite before or after.

My favorite part is the seating.  You can choose ahead of time your seat location and they have several spots for wheelchair access. The seats are recliners, which was quite comfortable... especially as I am disabled.

As for the staff, I encountered several and they were all very polite.

The only drawbacks I saw during my visit was the crazy long, long lines at the concession counter which moved very slowly.  My server seemed as if I were talking to a robot and annoyed by the couple of questions I had about their items. But when she went to get my order, she and another employee seemed to have acquired a happier personality until she returned with my order. Once I'd paid for my items, I felt rushed to leave. Unfortunately, I am disabled and can only carry my items in one hand and use my pockets for smaller items. She was young and maybe this is her first job; I can understand that. But maybe a different change of positions (i.e. ticket taker) may suit her personality better.

Overall, I had a great experience with the one exception, which I will overlook because almost all other visits there were spot on.

‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ 5 star overall rating.<//Text>

< Text>
I really do like this theater. However, they are understaffed at the ticket window and the concession stand. They need to hire at least 10 more people to work during the busy times. I always get fandango tickets, but I usually end up waiting another 20 minutes just to get through concessions. And now they are checking purses, which takes even longer. The management is not very good.

I do love coming here for the seats, the convenience of location, and to enjoy a movie. But they need to figure out how to have enough people working to make things run smoother. There are about 6 ticket windows, they should all be open on a weekend or other busy times.<//Text>

< review>
One of those fancy theaters where you choose your seating beforehand (like an airplane) and the seats have electronic adjustment and lean back, foot rest extends. The most liesurely way to watch "Welcome to my Neighborhood" on the big screen. The downside is the cost. $27 for me and the wife to go here, no snacks, matinee hours. The theater is great but I wouldn't go back for the cost alone. I don't know whether this theater accepts Moviepass.<//review>

<Rating>1<//Rating><Text>I've never had a decent experience at this theater. Having assigned seats instead of standard open seating makes it incredibly difficult get a halfway decent seat for yourself, unless you arrive hours before the movie starts, let alone get seats together when you go with family or friends.  The matinee tickets aren't terribly expensive but the senior and student discounts only apply after 4 pm which seems like a little bit of a copout.

I may have some bias as this new theater put my favorite small theater across the street out of business which had incredibly cheap tickets, food, and plenty of excess seating (people could show up right as the trailers were starting and still get a great seat), but I personally have never enjoyed a movie going experience at this theater. Try somewhere else or stick with Netflix.</Text><pictures>None<//pictures><response>None<//response>< gmapID>

< text>
BEWARE!  I went there on a Saturday, so it wasn't unusually crowded, and had to wait in line 20 minutes for popcorn/drinks.  Then, we had to wait in another line to get into the theaters, because they were checking everyone's purses.  They had a sign there by the podium (but NOT before you buy the tickets or wait in line for popcorn), that they were checking for security reasons.  But they weren't patting down the men, when 100% of theater shootings have been men, but just looking in women's purses.  That is a gross violation of privacy.  If they had really been concerned with security, they should focus on the men.  They were obviously using the shootings as an excuse to look for snacks being brought in the purses from outside.  Shame on you!  We missed the start of the movie because of this nonsense.< /text>

<name>Jeff Bullock< /name><Time>1449847327001< /Time><Rate>1< /Rate>< Review>
Everyone elses negative reviews hits it the nail on the head. I have seen a few of the staff just being rude. I don't know what people honestly think but this is their job. You wake up get dress and serve popcorn or print correct tickets. Ive had friends meet me then be kicked out later for a wrong ticket the front printed out. Heaven forbid you have to talk to them, because they will only make it sound like your fault. My main gripe is the the reserved seating bullshit (pardon my language). Countless times I've used fandango and ordered tickets (decent seating due to ordering a few days in advance). I'll check fandango and the computer out front of seat avalibility when the times comes because that's the person I am always checking random stuff like that. Fandango and the computer out front will show a fully booked theater only to end up being 1/5 full. The theater doesn't care because they already got their money from someone but if you wanted to walk in from the street like most people your "SOL". Ive broken the Taboo rule a few times and moved seats to a better area because they remained empty and i didn't want to crane my neck. FYI just pick the back 2 rows for movies the theater is so small they are almost perfect seats. Don't let the Fandango seating chart confuse you.< /Review>

<rating>5< /rating><response>None< /response>< Review>
Go here to see every movie, look people welcome to the future! If you don't like the reserved seating than you are just doing it wrong! I love it, buy my ticket hours before the showing and have basically empty theater to choose from usually, than show up right as the showing starts and no hassle just print your ticket at the machines by the customer service desk and enjoy! The food is 200% over charged but that's any movie theater so no whining at least they give you a refill on Large orders unlike Cinepolis! Have never once had a problem with fandango besides once which was user error cuz I didn't press confirm purchase. But ya really I am so glad movie theaters are catching up with the times because for someone who is an avid movie goer this makes life easy! now just make your food cheaper please!<//Review>

<username>Walter Macalma</username><Rating>4< /Rating>< Pics>

<Text>Regal Carlsbad is the love child of Cinepolis La Costa and Regal Oceanside. It‚Äôs got the lounging chairs, reserved seating and space of Cinepolis, but is more affordable with the more normal amenities of what people are more used to of a theater more than 3 years old.

Don‚Äôt get me wrong, when I go to Cinepolis it‚Äôs for cocktails, maybe some gastropub type food and a solid movie experience that is all you get what you pay for, but sometimes I don‚Äôt want to spend so much and don‚Äôt mind seeing a less than sold out matinee show, alone or whatever.

It‚Äôs actually smaller than I expected and in a good way I didn‚Äôt realize the expansion was really more for 24 as Luna and Regal could have easily been renovated without expansion.

I like the indoor ticketing, I like the auto kiosks. I like ordering via mobile since I have VIP rewards and I think there is better quality food. I‚Äôm glad they went with thinner more paper tickets. Probably saving a ton of money off just that little change. Plenty of parking.

I don‚Äôt like the bathrooms since they are basic, the hand dryers are super loud, I really wish places would have concessions closer to the theaters, maybe even behind the security portion. I don‚Äôt even use my tickets, I just show my phone now. Call me weird, but I like the seasoning powder and wish more places would carry it. They got me sneaking in my own seasoning here.

All in all it‚Äôs a great addition that has brought something back to the area. Lets face it when Mann and other theater left everyone went with them. I also think La Costa can service all of NCounty looking for full luxury. Prices are higher, service is better, it‚Äôs a new facility, but it‚Äôs still at ‚Äúthe mall‚Äù.</Text></record>
